[h2 id=RadicalSearchMethod 
	"Radical Search Method
	$LF
]h2
[div class=p 
	"Searching via radicals is typically the best way of finding unknown Kanji.  Radicals are pieces that make up Kanji.  Radicals should not be considered to have meaning.  Kanji that have meaning that are included in other Kanji are a far better measure for determining meaning. There are some bizarre Kanji that are simply extremely difficult to find using this method.  Common sense rules do not seem to apply.  But those are the exception.  Linking lots of potential sites to search for these since, some may or may not display right, and this will be  the most important tool to identify Kanji.
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"Single or Multi Radical Search.
	$LF
]div
[ul 
	[li 
		[a href=https://jisho.org/#radical rel=noopener external nofollow 
			"https://jisho.org/#radical
		]a
		$LF
	]li
]ul
[div class=p 
	"Another Single or Multi Radical Search.
	$LF
]div
[ul 
	[li 
		[a href=https://kanji.sljfaq.org/mr.html rel=noopener external nofollow 
			"https://kanji.sljfaq.org/mr.html
		]a
		$LF
	]li
]ul
[div class=p 
	"Single or Multi Radical Search.  Radicals are a little small on page, but the results are well displayed.
	$LF
]div
[ul 
	[li 
		[a href=https://www.nihongomaster.com/dictionary/kanji#p=1 rel=noopener external nofollow 
			"https://www.nihongomaster.com/dictionary/kanji#p=1
		]a
		$LF
	]li
]ul
[div class=p 
	"More in depth.
	$LF
]div
[ul 
	[li 
		[a href=https://www.nihongomaster.com/blog/what-are-kanji-radicals/ rel=noopener external nofollow 
			"https://www.nihongomaster.com/blog/what-are-kanji-radicals/
		]a
		$LF
	]li
]ul
[div class=p 
	"To find 車 I would maybe look at the center piece.  Let's see how that works....nope. square, square with two lines, vertical, horizontal lines all fail to find the Kanji.
	$LF
	"After finding the Kanji another way I found that the radical for the Kanji...IS the Kanji,  Which also happens and a possibility I overlooked since I did not recognize it as a radical.
	$LF
]div
[ul 
	[li 
		[a href=https://app.kanjialive.com/%E8%BB%8A rel=noopener external nofollow 
			"https://app.kanjialive.com/%E8%BB%8A
		]a
		$LF
	]li
	[li 
		[a href=https://jisho.org/search/%E8%BB%8A%20%23kanji rel=noopener external nofollow 
			"https://jisho.org/search/%E8%BB%8A%20%23kanji
		]a
		$LF
	]li
]ul
[div class=p 
	"So let's try finding 戦 via radicals.  Going to try use either the right or left side of this Kanji, since this is a Kanji that looks separated down the middle.  The right part is more simple so I will use that.  The right side turns out to be a 4 stroke radical.  That then brings up a list of possible Kanji.  Then 戦 looks like it has 13 strokes. I look in the results for the Kanji with 13 strokes and it is indeed in there.  
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"So for 戦 the radical search took seconds, and radical search for 車 could potentially be near instant if you considered that the Kanji could be the radical.
	$LF
]div
[ul 
	[li 
		[a href=https://kanji.sljfaq.org/mr.html rel=noopener external nofollow 
			"https://kanji.sljfaq.org/mr.html
		]a
		$LF
	]li
]ul
[h2 id=KanjiRadicalCompositionSearch 
	"Kanji Radical Composition Search
	$LF
]h2
[div class=p 
	"Kanji often share radicals. This can be used to find a different Kanji from one you already know.  One fairly unique thing that this tool does is Radical Decomposition of Kanji. Also can use multiple radicals to find Kanji.
	$LF
]div
[ul 
	[li 
		[a href=http://kanji.wareya.moe rel=noopener external nofollow 
			"http://kanji.wareya.moe
		]a
		$LF
	]li
]ul
[div class=p 
	"Ex: 軍陣	
	$LF
	"This word was chosen to use knowledge of radicals to identify kanji from one to another.
	$LF
	"軍陣【ぐんじん】		(n) camp, battlefield
	$LF
]div
[ol 
	[li 
		"Paste 軍
		$LF
	]li
	[li 
		"Select "Do Decomposition".
		$LF
	]li
	[li 
		"Select "Jouyou + Jinmeiyou" for the most common results.  "Found in media" can give a lot of uncommon results.  
		$LF
	]li
	[li 
		"Click Search
		$LF
	]li
	[li 
		"It gives the Radicals as below. Notice how 車 is now a radical in 軍?  The second Kanji in the word 戦車.
		$LF
	]li
]ol
[div class=p 
	"２：冖
	$LF
	"７：車
	$LF
]div
[ul 
	[li 
		[a href=http://kanji.wareya.moe/search?input=%E8%BB%8D&reverse=on&filter_level=media rel=noopener external nofollow 
			"http://kanji.wareya.moe/search?input=%E8%BB%8D&reverse=on&filter_level=media
		]a
		$LF
	]li
]ul
[div class=p 
	"Now let's find 陣 from the radical 車.
	$LF
]div
[ol 
	[li 
		"Click Clear
		$LF
	]li
	[li 
		"Paste in 車
		$LF
	]li
	[li 
		"Uncheck "Do Composition"
		$LF
	]li
	[li 
		"Select "Jouyou + Jinmeiyou" for the most common results.
		$LF
	]li
	[li 
		"Click Search
		$LF
	]li
	[li 
		"Under 9 strokes you can see that the fourth result is the Kanji we were attempting to find.
		$LF
	]li
]ol
[div class=p 
	"９：俥軌軍陣
	$LF
]div
[ul 
	[li 
		[a href=http://kanji.wareya.moe/search?input=%E8%BB%8A&filter_level=media rel=noopener external nofollow 
			"http://kanji.wareya.moe/search?input=%E8%BB%8A&filter_level=media
		]a
		$LF
	]li
]ul
[div class=p 
	"To find 陣 using radicals.
	$LF
]div
[ol 
	[li 
		"Click the button "clear" to remove previous results.
		$LF
	]li
	[li 
		"Click the 3 stroke radical 阝on the right side of the page in the radicals list.
		$LF
	]li
	[li 
		"Click the 7 stroke radical 車.
		$LF
	]li
	[li 
		"You should have found the exact 9 stroke Kanji 陣
		$LF
	]li
]ol
[ul 
	[li 
		[a href=http://kanji.wareya.moe/search?input=%E9%98%9D%E8%BB%8A&filter_level=media rel=noopener external nofollow 
